description:
&lt;p&gt;Blackpool Teaching Hospitals NHS FT is situated in the busy, vibrant, town of Blackpool where regeneration of the town is actively moving forward. As a busy holiday destination we have plenty to see and do including Blackpool Tower and Ballroom, bars, cafes and restaurants and theatres with major West End productions. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Close to the Lake District, a walker’s paradise, Manchester and Liverpool, providing airports close at hand, Blackpool is home to both young &amp; senior professionals, families and couples. With plenty to offer both in and out of the workplace, Blackpool Teaching Hospitals can provide the professional standards of quality and commitment to you.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Full Time and Part time posts are available offering exciting opportunities to join us in our busy and transforming Emergency Department.&lt;br /&gt;Our department covers and provides a service to a population of approximately 450,000 residents, increasing during our busy holiday seasons. &lt;br /&gt;The learning and development opportunities are vast with a dedicated training and development nurse in the department. We offer both internal and external courses to help you to develop to your full potential in Emergency nursing.&lt;br /&gt;We consider the Department to be an innovative creative and friendly environment for those nurses who wish to provide high quality patient centred care. &lt;br /&gt;Our team includes Advanced Nurse Practitioners, ENP’s, Mental Health Liaison, Nurse led thrombolysis team, Occupational therapists and physiotherapists.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You must,&lt;br /&gt;• Be a Registered nurse with 6 months post registration experience &lt;br /&gt;• Previous Emergency Nursing experience preferable.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We can offer you,&lt;br /&gt;• A modern forward thinking department with dedicated paediatric facilities providing 24 hour service.&lt;br /&gt;• Excellent opportunities for professional development supported by our own programmes tailored to meet your needs.&lt;br /&gt;• Clinical supervision, Preceptorship and Mentorship.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Internal rotation to night duty is a requirement of the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;These positions are available to Student Nurses, we would also welcome applicants who are interested in a Secondment Opportunity.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexible Working Patterns may also be available upon discussion, such as Night Shifts or Part-time hours, please discuss at Interview stage.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
